src: 좋아요, 그럼 시작해봅시다.
mt: Okay, then let's start.
ref: Okay, then let's start.

src: 죄송하지만 아기를 위한 메뉴는 없습니다.
mt: I'm sorry, but there's no menu for babies.
ref: Sorry, there's no menu available for babies.

src: 오늘 상무님 스케줄 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know the executive director's schedule today.
ref: Could you let me know the executive director's schedule for today?

src: 와 나무로 작업을 하시는구나.
mt: You're working with trees.
ref: Wow, you work with wood.

src: 그리고 색상도 바꿀 수 있어요.
mt: And you can also change the color.
ref: And you can change the color too.

src: 외국에서의 예술과 문화는 어땠나요?
mt: How was art and culture in foreign countries?
ref: What was art and culture like abroad?

src: 외국인 직원의 정규 고용은 가능합니다.
mt: Regular employment of foreign employees is possible.
ref: Regular employment of foreign employees is possible.

src: 시장이랑 종합 쇼핑몰 좋아하세요?
mt: Do you like markets and general shopping malls?
ref: Do you like markets and shopping malls?

src: 우리 회사는 글로벌 진출을 계획 중이다.
mt: Our company is planning to enter the global market.
ref: Our company is planning to expand globally.

src: 회사에서 교통비 전액을 지원해 드립니다.
mt: The company provides full transportation expenses.
ref: The company will cover all transportation expenses.

src: 그리고 경쟁사와 차별화된 점은 무엇인가요?
mt: And what's different from your competitors?
ref: And what sets you apart from your competitors?

src: 기본적으로, 근무 시간은 동일합니다.
mt: Basically, working hours are the same.
ref: Basically, the working hours are the same.

src: 롯데월드 타워도 꼭 방문해보세요.
mt: Be sure to visit Lotte World Tower.
ref: Be sure to visit Lotte World Tower too.

src: 호텔 이용객이라면 누구나 사용이 가능합니다.
mt: Any hotel user can use it.
ref: Anyone staying at the hotel can use it.

src: 우선 경복궁역에서 지하철을 타세요.
mt: First, take the subway at Gyeongbokgung station.
ref: First, take the subway from Gyeongbokgung Station.

src: 혹시 선호하시는 디자인이 특별히 있으신가요?
mt: Do you have any particular design you prefer?
ref: Do you have a particular design that you prefer?"

src: 저희 학교에서 함께 일하게 되면 좋겠습니다.
mt: I hope we can work together at our school.
ref: I hope we can work together at our school.

src: 혹시 어떤 주제로 시작하고 싶으신가요?
mt: What topic do you want to start with?
ref: What topic would you like to start with ?

src: 요즘 유행하는 엠지 단어 알려줘.
mt: Tell me the word MG that is popular these days.
ref: Tell me some trendy MG words these days.

src: 클라우드 기반의 앱의 장점은 무엇인가요?
mt: What are the advantages of cloud-based apps?
ref: What are the benefits of cloud-based apps?

src: 그리고 특정 브랜드에 대한 선호도가 있나요?
mt: And do you have a preference for a specific brand?
ref: And do you have any preferences for specific brands?

src: 이제 우리는 조각 작업을 시작할 거에요.
mt: Now we are going to start sculpture work.
ref: Now we are going to start the sculpting work.

src: 국제시장에 아주 유명한 가게가 있어요.
mt: There is a very famous store in the international market.
ref: There is a very famous store in Gukje Market.

src: 네, 여기 안내 지도를 드릴게요.
mt: Yes, I'll give you a guide map.
ref: Yes, here's a guide map for you.

src: 부산에 오면 해산물을 먹어야죠.
mt: You have to eat seafood when you come to Busan.
ref: When you come to Busan, you have to eat seafood.

src: 저는 주로 풍경 그림을 그리는 편이에요.
mt: I usually draw landscapes.
ref: I usually paint landscapes.

src: 혹시 여행자 보험 가입돼 있으세요?
mt: Do you have traveler's insurance?
ref: Do you have travel insurance?

src: 스탠다드가 가장 기본적인 객실이에요.
mt: Standard is the most basic room.
ref: Standard is the most basic room.

src: 마이크로소프트 업데이트를 하려면 어떻게 해야 돼?
mt: What should I do to update Microsoft?
ref: How do I get Microsoft updates?

src: 전통과 현대를 조화롭게 표현하고 있네요.
mt: It expresses tradition and modernity in harmony.
ref: It harmoniously expresses tradition and modernity.

src: 각각의 돌은 고유한 특성을 가지고 있어요.
mt: Each stone has its own characteristics.
ref: Each stone has its own unique properties.

src: 저는 이 학교에서 경영학을 공부하고 있습니다.
mt: I'm studying business administration at this school.
ref: I am studying business administration at this school.

src: 네. 해운대까지 모셔 드리겠습니다.
mt: Okay. I'll take you to Haeundae.
ref: Yes. I will take you to Haeundae.

src: 상대방을 가스라이팅한다는 의미는 뭐야?
mt: What does it mean to gas your opponent?
ref: What does it mean to gaslight someone?

src: 오늘 디지털 아트의 기초를 배울 것입니다.
mt: I will learn the basics of digital art today.
ref: Today we will learn the basics of digital art.

src: 시장은 확실히 활기가 있어서 좋구요.
mt: It's good that the market is definitely lively.
ref: The market is definitely lively, which is nice.

src: 알파벳과 구글의 관계에 대해서 설명해줘.
mt: Explain the relationship between the alphabet and Google.
ref: Explain the relationship between Alphabet and Google.

src: 홍보팀에서의 업무 내용은 어떻게 되나요?
mt: What's the details of your work in the PR team?
ref: What kind of work does the PR team handle?

src: 강남에도 늦게까지 하는 상점이 많아요.
mt: There are many shops in Gangnam that are open until late.
ref: There are many stores in Gangnam that are open late.

src: 하이브리드랑 전기차가 같은 뜻인가?
mt: Does hybrid mean the same thing as electric cars?
ref: Do hybrid cars and electric cars mean the same thing?

src: 연락처는 별도로 메일로 전달드리도록 하겠습니다.
mt: I will send you the contact information separately by e-mail.
ref: We will send you the contact information separately via email.

src: 다음 주에 계약서 관련하여 다시 연락 드리겠습니다.
mt: I will contact you again about the contract next week.
ref: I will follow up with you next week regarding the contract.

src: 유럽에 진출한 해외 글로벌 기업 좀 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know the overseas global companies that have entered Europe.
ref: Tell me about some global companies that have advanced into Europe.

src: 원하시는 언어로 진행되는 수업을 선택할 수 있어요.
mt: You can choose a class in the language you want.
ref: You can choose a class taught in the language of your choice.

src: 먼저 디지털 아트 수업에 참석해 주셔서 감사합니다.
mt: First of all, thank you for attending the digital art class.
ref: First of all, thank you for attending the digital art class.

src: 인도네시아 수도 자카르타 여행 정보 좀 알려줘.
mt: Please tell me the travel information of Jakarta, the capital of Indonesia.
ref: Please give me some travel information about Jakarta, the capital of Indonesia.

src: 가능하다면 미리 전화로 예약하시는 게 좋아요.
mt: If possible, you'd better make a reservation by phone in advance.
ref: If possible, it's best to make a reservation by phone in advance.

src: 데이터베이스와 데이터 아키텍트의 정의를 알려줘.
mt: Let me know the definition of database and data architecture.
ref: Please define database and data architect.

src: 플레이스테이션의 세일은 언제 하나요?
mt: When is the PlayStation sale?
ref: When is the PlayStation sale?

src: 이 에어라인은 홈페이지에서 예약을 지원합니다.
mt: This airline supports reservations on the homepage.
ref: This airline supports reservations on its website.

src: 정상에서 바라보는 풍경은 정말로 마법 같아요.
mt: The view from the top is really magical.
ref: The view from the top is truly magical.

src: 여기 오셨다니 잘 선택하셨네요.
mt: You've made a good choice since you're here.
ref: You made a good choice by coming here.

src: 난징에 있는 박물관에 갔다 왔어?
mt: Did you go to a museum in Nanjing?
ref: Have you been to the museum in Nanjing?

src: 와, 저도 이렇게 또 배우게 되네요
mt: Wow, I'm learning again like this.
ref: Wow, I'm learning something like this again

src: 테무와 알리의 다른 점은 무엇인가요?
mt: What is the difference between Timu and Ali?
ref: What is the difference between Temu and Ali?

src: 트럼프와 머스크는 어떤 관련이 있는지 알아?
mt: Do you know how Trump and Musk are related?
ref: Do you know how Trump and Musk are related?

src: 전기차랑 하이브리드 차의 차이점을 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know the difference between an electric car and a hybrid car.
ref: Tell me the difference between electric and hybrid cars.

src: 그래서 원하시는 난이도에 맞게 선택하시면 좋아요.
mt: So you can choose according to the level of difficulty you want.
ref: So, please choose according to your desired difficulty level.

src: 이게 바로 지금 제가 하고 있는 작업입니다.
mt: This is what I'm doing now.
ref: This is what I'm working on right now.

src: 이 작품은 전통과 현대의 조화를 아름답게 보여주고 있어요.
mt: This work shows a beautiful harmony between tradition and modern times.
ref: This work beautifully demonstrates the harmony between tradition and modernity.

src: 최대한 빠르게 양질의 서비스를 제공하려 노력하고 있습니다.
mt: We are trying to provide quality services as soon as possible.
ref: We strive to provide quality service as quickly as possible.

src: 실적이 좋은 회사의 스톡 옵션을 구입했어.
mt: I bought the stock option of a company with good performance.
ref: I bought stock options from a company with strong performance.

src: 이 버튼을 클릭하면 프레젠테이션이 진행되나요?
mt: Does the presentation take place if I click this button?
ref: If I click this button, will the presentation proceed?

src: 그래야 제가 적합한 제품을 추천해 드릴 수 있어서요.
mt: That way, I can recommend a suitable product.
ref: This way, I can recommend the right product for you.

src: 알겠습니다. 이제 말씀하신 모든 제품 준비해 드릴게요.
mt: Okay. Now I will prepare all the products you mentioned.
ref: Okay, I'll prepare all the products you mentioned.

src: 그럼 이곳에 필요한 도구와 색상을 준비할까요?
mt: Then should we prepare the necessary tools and colors here?
ref: So, shall we prepare the tools and colors needed here?

src: 제주 민속공예품도 한번 구경해보세요.
mt: Look around Jeju folk crafts too.
ref: Be sure to check out Jeju's folk crafts too.

src: 에이 기업은 어떤 부분에서 가장 자부심을 가지고 있나요?
mt: What part of A company is the most proud of?
ref: What part of its business is Company A most proud of?

src: 어떤 이야기를 이 작품으로 전달하고 싶으셨나요?
mt: What story did you want to tell about with this work?
ref: What kind of story did you want to convey through this work?

src: 특히 날씨가 맑은 날에는 동해까지 보이기도 해요.
mt: Especially on clear days, we can see the East Sea.
ref: Especially on clear days, you can even see the East Sea.

src: 지금 엔비디아 주가에 대해서 알려주세요.
mt: Please tell me about Nvidia's stock price now.
ref: Please tell me about Nvidia stock price right now.

src: 아 그러시구나, 정말 반갑습니다.
mt: Oh, I see, nice to see you.
ref: Oh, I see. It's really nice to meet you.

src: 모든 것을 천천히 배울 테니 너무 걱정하지 마세요.
mt: I will learn everything slowly, so don't worry too much.
ref: Don't worry too much, you'll learn everything slowly.

src: 비비씨가 어느 나라 방송국이라고 했지?
mt: Which broadcasting station in which country did you say BB?
ref: Which country's broadcasting station did the BBC say it was from?

src: 베트남 호치민이라는 도시는 여행하기에 어때?
mt: How about traveling to Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam?
ref: How about traveling to the city of Ho Chi Minh City in Vietnam?

src: 정직원 전환 절차는 일반적으로 다음과 같습니다.
mt: The transition process for full-time employees is generally as follows.
ref: The process for converting to a full-time employee is generally as follows:

src: 파이썬 코드를 공부하는 법에 관련된 책이 있을까?
mt: Do you have any books related to how to study the pason code?
ref: Do you know any books that teach you how to study Python programming?

src: 그렇게 생각하니 투자의 가치가 있는 작업이네요.
mt: That's what I think is worth investing.
ref: When I think about it that way, it seems like a worthwhile investment.

src: 로제의 신곡 아파트 가사 좀 알려줄래?
mt: Could you tell me the lyrics of Rose's new apartment?
ref: Can you tell me the lyrics to Rosé's new song, Apartment?

src: 하노이를 여행하려고 하는데 괜찮은 호텔을 알려줘.
mt: I'm going to travel to Hanoi, so please let me know a nice hotel.
ref: I'm planning to travel to Hanoi. Can you recommend a good hotel?

src: 어쿠스틱 음악들 플레이리스트 만들어줘.
mt: Make acoustic music playlists.
ref: Make a playlist of acoustic music.

src: 제 영감은 서울 주변의 아름다운 장면들이에요.
mt: My inspiration is beautiful scenes around Seoul.
ref: My inspiration is the beautiful scenes around Seoul.

src: 통역사를 동원한다는 것은 추가적인 비용이 발생하게 됩니다.
mt: Using an interpreter will incur additional costs.
ref: Hiring an interpreter will incur additional costs.

src: 블랙프라이데이 때 세일하는 항목은 무엇인가요?
mt: What are the sales items on Black Friday?
ref: What items are on sale on Black Friday?

src: 이 그림은 정말로 감정과 느낌을 잘 담아냈네요.
mt: This picture really captures emotions and feelings well.
ref: This painting truly captures the emotions and feelings beautifully.

src: 중복되는 메뉴도 있고 다른 메뉴도 있습니다.
mt: There are overlapping menus and other menus.
ref: There are some duplicate menus and some different menus.

src: 임시 여권을 발급받기 위해서는 여러 가지 서류가 필요해요.
mt: Various documents are needed to get a temporary passport issued.
ref: Various documents are required to get a temporary passport.

src: 호텔이나 가이드 관련해서 요구사항 있으실까요?
mt: Do you have any requirements regarding hotels or guides?
ref: Do you have any requests regarding hotels or guides?

src: 어플리케이션을 업데이트하는 시간은 얼마나 소요될까요?
mt: How long will it take to update the application?
ref: How long will it take to update the application?

src: 발리에서 수영하기 가장 좋은 명소를 알려줘.
mt: Tell me the best place to swim in Bali.
ref: Tell me the best places to swim in Bali.

src: 보통 헤드헌터는 연봉이 어느 정도 되니?
mt: How much is the annual salary for headhunters?
ref: How much does a headhunter usually earn?

src: 글로벌 컴퓨팅 플랫폼 중 대표적인 기업 다섯가지를 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know 5 representative companies among the global computing platforms.
ref: Tell me five leading companies in global computing platforms.

src: 오늘 피피티로 자기소개 자료를 만들었어.
mt: I made a self-introduction material on PPT today.
ref: Today I made a self-introduction using PPT.

src: 시간 내에 받은 주문만 서비스 제공이 가능합니다.
mt: Only orders received in time can be provided with services.
ref: Only orders placed within the time limit can be serviced.

src: 그럼 돼지국밥도 꼭 드셔보세요.
mt: Then make sure to try pork soup.
ref: Then make sure to try the pork rice soup too.

src: 구글은 클라우드 서비스를 무료로 제공하고 있다는데 사실이야?
mt: Is it true that Google is offering cloud services for free?
ref: Is it true that Google offers cloud services for free?

src: 케이피아이를 쿼터별로 설정하는 방법을 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know how to set K-Pia for each quarter.
ref: Please tell me how to set KPI by quarter.

src: 미팅 일정을 다시 디벨롭 해서 정리해줘.
mt: Please send the meeting schedule back to the default and arrange it.
ref: Please re-develop and organize the meeting schedule.

src: 저희도 함께 작업하고 새로운 기술과 기법을 배우고 있어요.
mt: We are also working together and learning new technologies and techniques.
ref: We are also working together and learning new technologies and techniques.

src: 전기차 중에 아이오닉 전기차가 유명해?
mt: Are Ionic electric cars famous among electric vehicles?
ref: Is the Ioniq electric car famous among electric vehicles?

src: 효율적인 트래픽 관리를 위해 라우팅 알고리즘을 도입했다.
mt: For efficient traffic management, a routing algorithm has been introduced.
ref: To optimize traffic management, a routing algorithm was introduced.

src: 네. 남은 여행도 무사히 즐기시길요.
mt: Yes. Enjoy the rest of your trip safely.
ref: Yes. I hope you enjoy the rest of your trip.

src: 회사의 국제적인 비즈니스 확장에 대해 어떻게 생각하나요?
mt: What do you think about the company's international business expansion?
ref: What do you think about the company's international business expansion?

src: 원 밀리언 달러는 현재 환율이 어떻게 돼?
mt: What is the current exchange rate for one million dollars?
ref: What is the current exchange rate for One Million Dollars?

src: 제안서 작성 전에 메모로 정리해 줄래?
mt: Would you please organize it with a memo before writing the proposal?
ref: Could you please organize this into a memo before writing the proposal?

src: 구글에서 이용할 수 있는 클라우드 서비스가 있다면 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know if there is a cloud service available on Google.
ref: Let me know if there are any cloud services available from Google.

src: 글로벌 시장에 진출하기 위해 필요한 주요 요소들을 알려주세요.
mt: Please let me know the main factors needed to enter the global market.
ref: Please tell me the key elements needed to enter the global market.

src: 글로벌 마켓 시장에서 네이티브 스피커의 장점을 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know the advantages of native speakers in the global market.
ref: Tell me about the advantages of native speakers in the global market.

src: 혹시, 연구개발팀과의 협업 기회도 많나요?
mt: Do you have many opportunities to collaborate with the research and development team?
ref: Are there many opportunities to collaborate with the research and development team?

src: 나는 우리 회사의 프로젝트를 비딩할 준비가 됐어.
mt: I'm ready to cover our company's project.
ref: I'm ready to bid on our company's project.

src: 나는 요즘 노션을 이용해서 회의록을 작성하고 있어.
mt: I'm writing a meeting book using a mission these days.
ref: I'm using Notion to write meeting minutes these days.

src: 그런데 이 부분은 어떤 붓을 사용해서 그린거야?
mt: By the way, which brush did you use to draw this part?
ref: By the way, what brush did you use to paint this part?

src: 오늘 수업에서는 어떤 주제로 시작하길 원하시나요?
mt: What kind of subject do you want to start in today's class?
ref: What topic would you like to start with in today's class?

src: 예를 들면, 부장님의 의견도 매우 중요하게 생각합니다.
mt: For example, the manager's opinion is also very important.
ref: For example, I also consider the manager's opinion very important.

src: 새로운 디자인을 만들어 특허를 받으려면 어떻게 해야 되나요?
mt: What should I do to make a new design and get a patent?
ref: How do I create a new design and get a patent for it?

src: 이번 자라 디자이너 중에 명품 회사에서 일했던 사람 있어?
mt: Is there anyone who worked for a luxury company among this Zara designers?
ref: Are there any Zara designers who have worked for luxury companies?

src: 원하시는 시간대와 요일에 따라 다를 수 있어요.
mt: It may vary depending on the time zone and day of the week you want.
ref: It may vary depending on your preferred time zone and day of the week.

src: 모임 일정이 잡히는 대로 이메일로 알려드리도록 하겠습니다.
mt: I will let you know by e-mail as soon as the meeting schedule is set.
ref: We will notify you by email as soon as the meeting schedule is set.

src: 그리고 연속 수강 시 혜택에 대해서도 알려드릴게요.
mt: And I'll let you know the benefits of continuous classes.
ref: And I'll also let you know about the benefits of continuous enrollment.

src: 베트남 다낭과 같은 항구 도시 여행 정보 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know the travel information of the port cities like Danang, Vietnam.
ref: Please tell me about travel information for port cities like Da Nang, Vietnam.

src: 와이파이 없이 통신을 원활하게 하는 방법이 있는지 알려주세요.
mt: Please let me know if there is a way to communicate smoothly without Wi-Fi.
ref: Please let me know if there is a way to communicate smoothly without wifi.

src: 조사한 데이터를 바탕으로 우리 부서의 문제점을 파악해줘.
mt: Please identify the problems of our department based on the data we researched.
ref: Based on the data you have collected, identify the problems in our department.

src: 마이크로소프트 업데이트하고 싶은데 어떻게 하면 되는지 알려줄래?
mt: I want to update Microsoft, can you tell me what to do?
ref: I want to update Microsoft, can you tell me how to do that?

src: 아 그러셨구나, 진짜 잘 오셨습니다.
mt: Oh, I see, I'm so glad you're here.
ref: Oh, I see. I'm really glad you're here.

src: 일본 도요타 회사에서 나오는 전기차가 무엇인지 알려줘.
mt: Please tell me what electric cars are coming out of Toyota company in Japan.
ref: Tell me what kind of electric car is coming out from Toyota, Japan.

src: 발리는 인도네시아의 섬 명소라던데, 맞아?
mt: I heard that Bali is an island attraction in Indonesia, is that correct?
ref: I heard that Bali is a famous island destination in Indonesia. is that right?

src: 베트남에 가서 무역을 해보고 싶은데 어떻게 생각하니?
mt: I want to trade in Vietnam, what do you think?
ref: I want to go to Vietnam and do some trading. What do you think?

src: 저작권에 걸리지 않는 일러스트가 필요한데 사이트를 알려주세요.
mt: I need an illustration that doesn't get copyrighted, so please let me know the site.
ref: I need illustrations that are not copyrighted. Please let me know the site.

src: 그럼 이렇게 조화롭게 결합하는 것이 좋아 보이네요.
mt: Then it looks good to combine in harmony like this.
ref: Well, it looks like it would be nice to combine them harmoniously like this.

src: 스타트업 창업을 생각 중인데 팀빌딩 피드백을 받고 싶어.
mt: I'm thinking of starting a startup, but I want to get feedback on the team building.
ref: I'm thinking about starting a startup, and I'd like some feedback on team building.

src: 현재의 복리후생 혜택은 지속적으로 유지될 예정입니다.
mt: The current benefits of welfare will continue to be maintained.
ref: Current welfare benefits will continue to be maintained.

src: 이제 그림을 좀 더 디테일하게 만들어볼까요?
mt: Shall we make the picture more detailed now?
ref: Shall we make the drawing more detailed now?

src: 여러 레이어를 조립하여 복잡한 장면을 만들 수 있습니다.
mt: You can make complicated scenes by assembling multiple layers.
ref: You can create complex scenes by assembling multiple layers.

src: 와이탄에서 볼 만한 관광지를 추천해줄래?
mt: Could you recommend some tourist attractions to visit in Witan?
ref: Can you recommend some tourist attractions in Waitan?

src: 지난번 프로젝트에서 발생했던 최대 아웃풋은 뭐야?
mt: What is the biggest output that occurred in the last project?
ref: What was the maximum output from the last project?

src: 웨이신은 텐센트가 개발한 소셜 커뮤니케이션 플랫폼이야.
mt: Weixin is a social communication platform developed by Tencent.
ref: WeChat is a social communication platform developed by Tencent.

src: 현재 마사지는 사일 월요일로 예약되어 있습니다.
mt: Currently, massage is booked for private Monday.
ref: Massages are currently booked for Monday the 4th.

src: 가스라이팅의 의미에 대해서 알려줄 수 있을까?
mt: Can you tell me about the meaning of gas lighting?
ref: Can you tell me the meaning of gaslighting?

src: 지마켓이랑 쿠팡 중에 뭐가 더 쿠폰을 많이 받아?
mt: Which coupons do you get more, Gmarket or Coupang?
ref: Which one gives more coupons, Gmarket or Coupang?

src: 방금 다운받은 어플리케이션에 업데이트가 끝나지 않아요.
mt: The update is not over on the application I just downloaded.
ref: The application I just downloaded won't finish updating.

src: 플로리다의 잭슨빌은 관광지로서 어때?
mt: How about Jacksonville in Florida as a tourist destination?
ref: How about Jacksonville, Florida as a tourist destination?

src: 프레젠테이션에서 클릭 한번으로 애니메이션 효과를 추가할 수 있습니다.
mt: You can add animation effects with just one click from the presentation.
ref: Add animation effects to your presentations with just one click.

src: 쇼핑몰 웹디자이너는 보통 어떤 편집 프로그램을 써?
mt: What kind of editing program does a shopping mall web designer usually use?
ref: What editing program do shopping mall web designers usually use?

src: 난징에 있는 박물관을 같이 관람하러 갈래?
mt: Do you want to visit the museum in Nanjing together?
ref: Would you like to go see the museum in Nanjing together?

src: 너 항저우 여행 갔을 때 호수도 갔었어?
mt: Did you go to the lake when you went on a trip to Hangzhou?
ref: Did you go to the lake when you traveled to Hangzhou?

src: 이번 연도 유니콘 기업들의 최대 실적 성과들을 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know the best performance of unicorn companies this year.
ref: Tell me about the best performances of unicorn companies this year.

src: 디비 엔진이 다양한 데이터 모델러가 뭐가 있을까?
mt: What are the various data models for the DB engine?
ref: What are the different data modelers that DB Engine has?

src: 재계약 협의 시에 그 부분도 포함해서 논의해보겠습니다.
mt: We will discuss it including that part when discussing the renewal of the contract.
ref: We will discuss that part as well during the contract renewal negotiations.

src: 크리스마스엔 혼자서 촌캉스에 도전해볼까 해.
mt: I'm thinking of taking on a vacation alone on Christmas.
ref: I'm thinking about trying a country vacation alone for Christmas.

src: 시카고에서 가족 사인이 묵을 만한 호텔을 추천해줘.
mt: Please recommend a hotel in Chicago where my family can stay.
ref: Recommend me a hotel in Chicago where my family can stay.

src: 호텔 조식으로 스크램블 말고 또 뭐가 나와?
mt: What else is there other than scrambles for breakfast at the hotel?
ref: What else do hotels serve for breakfast besides scrambled eggs?

src: 반지르에서 추천할 만한 도시의 명소는 무엇인가요?
mt: What are the famous places in the city recommended by Bandre?
ref: What are some city attractions you would recommend in Banjul?

src: 중국 난징에 있는 박물관을 한번 가보고 싶어.
mt: I want to visit a museum in Nanjing, China.
ref: I'd like to visit a museum in Nanjing, China.

src: 내가 올려주는 데이터를 분석해서 결과를 알려줄 수 있어?
mt: Can you tell me the result after analyzing the data I uploaded?
ref: Can you analyze the data I upload and tell me the results?

src: 미서부 여행으로 그랜드 캐니언이 유명해?
mt: Is Grand Canyon famous for traveling west-west?
ref: Is the Grand Canyon famous for trips to the West Coast?

src: 힙스터들이 많이 가는 맛집 추천해줄 수 있어?
mt: Can you recommend me a good restaurant that many hipsters go to?
ref: Can you recommend a restaurant that a lot of hipsters go to?

src: 에이아이 챗봇 미드저니 사용 방법을 알려줄래?
mt: Could you tell me how to use AI chatbot Midzani?
ref: Can you tell me how to use AI Chatbot Midjourney?

src: 네, 이렇게 함께 해주신다니 정말 영광입니다.
mt: Yes, it's an honor to be with you like this.
ref: Yes, it's truly an honor to have you with us.

src: 모든 활동과 식사 포함하여 일인당 팔십만원입니다.
mt: It's 80 million won per person, including all activities and meals.
ref: It costs eight hundred thousand won per person, including all activities and meals.

src: 상무님 스케줄 확인해서 달력에 표시해줄래?
mt: Could you check the director's schedule and mark it on the calendar?
ref: Sir, could you please check my schedule and mark it on the calendar?

src: 홀리데이 시즌에 부산에서 가기 좋은 호텔을 추천해줘.
mt: Please recommend a good hotel to go to Busan during the holiday season.
ref: Please recommend a good hotel to stay at in Busan during the holiday season.

src: 해킹에 취약한 클라우드 환경의 주요 특징이 뭔지 좀 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know the main characteristics of the cloud environment that is vulnerable to hacking.
ref: Tell me some key characteristics of a cloud environment that are vulnerable to hacking.

src: 이번에 새롭게 설치한 미드저니의 사용 방법을 좀 알려주세요.
mt: Please tell me how to use the newly installed midzarie.
ref: Could you please tell me how to use the newly installed Midjourney?

src: 저는 유니콘 기업에 취직해서 좋은 성과를 내고 싶습니다.
mt: I want to get a job at a unicorn company and get good results.
ref: I want to get a job at a unicorn company and achieve great results.

src: 파이썬이랑 코드 공부하고 있는데 관련 책 소개해줘.
mt: I'm studying the code with Pason, so please introduce me to a related book.
ref: I'm studying Python and coding. Please recommend some related books.

src: 쓰촨의 명소와 음식이 맛있는 맛집을 알려줘.
mt: Please tell me the famous restaurants and restaurants in Sichuan that have delicious food.
ref: Please tell me about some famous attractions and great restaurants with delicious food in Sichuan.

src: 이월 달에 하노이에서 삼일 정도 묵을 호텔이 있을까?
mt: Will there be a hotel to stay in Hanoi for 3 days in this month?
ref: Are there any hotels I can stay at in Hanoi for three days in February?

src: 미드저니를 사용해보고 싶은데 기본적인 사용 방법을 알려줘.
mt: I'd like to try the mid-sized one, so please tell me the basic way to use it.
ref: I want to try Midjourney, please tell me the basic usage method.

src: 성과는 높고 일은 쉬운 그런 유니콘 기업 없을까?
mt: Isn't there such a unicorn company with high performance and easy work?
ref: Is there a unicorn company where the work is easy but the results are great?

src: 새로운 디자인을 만들었을 때 특허를 신청하는 방법을 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know how to apply for a patent when you make a new design.
ref: When I create a new design, please tell me how to apply for a patent.

src: 쿠타라는 해변에서 즐겁게 서핑해보고 싶어.
mt: I want to surf happily at the beach called Kuta.
ref: I’d love to have a fun surfing experience at a beach called Kuta.

src: 지난번 우리가 했던 프로젝트 아웃풋이 굉장히 좋던데?
mt: The project output we did last time was really good, right?
ref: The output of the project we did last time was really good, wasn't it?

src: 베트남 여행 가려고 하는데 하롱 베이 기후 좀 알려줘.
mt: I'm planning to go on a trip to Vietnam, so please tell me the climate in Halong Bay.
ref: I'm planning a trip to Vietnam, so can you tell me what the climate is like in Ha Long Bay?

src: 설악산에는 다양한 난이도의 코스가 마련되어 있는데요.
mt: Seoraksan Mountain has a variety of difficult courses.
ref: Seoraksan Mountain has courses of various difficulty levels.

src: 에이아이로 그린 일러스트는 저작권을 침해하는 것일까?
mt: Does illustration drawn with an AI infringe on copyright?
ref: Do AI-generated illustrations infringe on copyright?

src: 트렌드는 어떤 걸 기준 지표로 삼아서 만드는 거야?
mt: What kind of trend is made by using it as a reference index?
ref: What is the standard indicator used to create trends?

src: 엠비티아이 잇프제의 특성에 대해서 설명해 주세요.
mt: Please explain about the characteristics of the MBI gum.
ref: Please explain the characteristics of MBTI IFPJ.

src: 줄임말 엠지는 뭐의 줄임말일까?
mt: What does the short term MG mean?
ref: What does the abbreviation 'MG' stand for?

src: 어쿠스틱 장르의 노래를 플레이리스트로 만들어줄래?
mt: Could you make the acoustic genre song a playlist?
ref: Could you make a playlist of acoustic genre songs?

src: 팀 본딩은 팀플과 다른 의미가 있는 거야?
mt: Does Team bonding have a different meaning than Team People?
ref: Does team bonding have a different meaning than team play?

src: 일반적으로 대사관은 오전 아홉시부터 오후 다섯시까지 운영해요.
mt: In general, the embassy is open from 9 am to 5 pm.
ref: In general, embassies operate from 9 am to 5 pm.

src: 험블과 플렉스의 차이에 대해 알려줄 수 있을까?
mt: Can you tell me the difference between Hable and Flex?
ref: Can you tell me the difference between Humble and Flex?

src: 넷플릭스에서 로맨스 영화 추천해줄래? 달달한 걸로.
mt: Would you recommend a romance movie on Netflix? It's sweet.
ref: Can you recommend some romantic movies on Netflix? Something sweet.

src: 케이피아이 수립은 헤드쿼터에서 하는 업무야?
mt: Is setting up a KPI a task in the head quarter?
ref: Is establishing KPI a task that is done at headquarters?

src: 일론 머스크가 운영하는 테슬라를 제외한 다른 회사를 알려줘.
mt: Tell me another company except Tesla run by Elon Musk.
ref: Tell me any other company besides Tesla run by Elon Musk.

src: 이 기사 스크랩해서 슬랙에 올려볼까?
mt: Shall we scrap this article and put it on the slack?
ref: Should I scrap this article and post it on Slack?

src: 스타트업 아이티 기업에서는 팀 빌딩을 어떻게 해야 할까?
mt: What should we do with a team building at a startup IT company?
ref: How should team building be approached in a startup IT company?

src: 그래피티와 색상 표현은 정말로 멋진 아트 스타일이죠.
mt: Grapiti and color expression are really wonderful art styles.
ref: Graffiti and color expression are really cool art styles.

src: 명확한 지시나 피드백 없이 일을 시작해야 하는 경우가 있거든.
mt: There are times when you have to start work without clear instructions or feedback.
ref: Sometimes you have to start a task without clear instructions or feedback.

src: 설악산은 자연이 풍부하게 그려진 명화 같은 곳이죠.
mt: Seoraksan is a famous place where nature is abundantly painted.
ref: Seoraksan is a place rich in nature, like a famous painting.

src: 제미니 어플 가장 최신 버전은 언제 나왔니?
mt: When did you get the latest version of the Jemini application?
ref: When was the latest version of the Gemini app released?

src: 나트랑에서 가장 큰 리조트를 알려줄 수 있니?
mt: Can you tell me the biggest resort in Natrang?
ref: Can you tell me the biggest resort in Nha Trang?

src: 모바일로 비행기 체크인하려고 하는데 좌석 지정할 수 있어?
mt: I want to check-in through mobile, can I choose a seat?
ref: If I check in on mobile, can I choose my seat?

src: 도시 호치민에서 가장 유명한 관광지는 어떤 곳인가요?
mt: What is the most famous tourist attraction in Ho Chi Minh City?
ref: What are the most famous tourist attractions in Ho Chi Minh City?

src: 현재 진행되고 있는 데이터 분석가 채용 공고 알려줄 수 있어?
mt: Can you tell me the job posting of the data analyst in progress?
ref: Can you let me know about any current data analyst job openings?

src: 지난 미팅 자료에서 디벨롭이라는 글자를 찾아줘.
mt: Please find the word developer in the last meeting.
ref: Find the word "develop" in the last meeting materials.

src: 스펙과 커리어의 상관관계를 예를 들어 설명해 주세요.
mt: Please explain, for example, the correlation between spec and career.
ref: Please explain the correlation between specs and career with an example.

src: 구글 크롬 브라우저를 쓰려면 확장 프로그램이 필요할까?
mt: Do I need an extension program to use Google Chrome browser?
ref: Do I need extensions to use the Google Chrome browser?

src: 중국에서 사업을 할 때에 <unk>시가 어느 정도 필요할까?
mt: How much do you need when doing business in China?
ref: How much guanxi is needed when doing business in China?

src: 월 이십만 원의 지방근무 수당이 지급됩니다.
mt: A monthly allowance of two hundred thousand won is paid for local work.
ref: A local work allowance of two hundred thousand won per month is paid.

src: 그렇게 생각하신다면 연속 수강은 훌륭한 선택일 것입니다.
mt: If you think so, continuous classes will be a great choice.
ref: If you think so, taking consecutive classes would be a great choice.

src: 여기에서는 다양한 등산로를 통해 다양한 경험을 할 수 있어요.
mt: You can experience various things here through various hiking trails.
ref: Here, you can have a variety of experiences through various hiking trails.

src: 파이브가이즈에서 판매하는 쉐이크의 가격을 알려줄래?
mt: Could you tell me the price of the shake sold by Five Kids?
ref: Can you tell me the price of a shake sold at Five Guys?

src: 여기 호텔에서는 룸 서비스가 모두 무료가 아닌 유료야.
mt: In this hotel, all room services are not free, but paid.
ref: In this hotel, room service is not free; it is paid.

src: 줌을 활용한 미팅에서 자주 발생하는 문제와 해결책은 무엇인가요?
mt: What are the problems and solutions that occur frequently in meetings using zoom?
ref: What are some common problems and solutions for meetings using Zoom?

src: 임시 여권을 발급받으면 여행 일정을 계속 진행할 수 있습니다.
mt: If you get a temporary passport, you can continue your travel schedule.
ref: Once you have your temporary passport, you can continue with your travel plans.

src: 대만 여행에서 기념품인 펑리수를 사 왔어.
mt: I bought Peng Li Su, a souvenir, from my trip to Taiwan.
ref: I bought some fengli cakes as a souvenir from my trip to Taiwan.

src: 쿠팡과 스마트스토어 어디에 입점하는 게 더 수익이 될까요?
mt: Where will it be more profitable to enter Coupang and Smart Store?
ref: Where would be more profitable to open a store, Coupang or Smart Store?

src: 저장한 파일을 볼 수 있는 디렉토리는 무엇인지 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know what directory you can see the saved file.
ref: Can you let me know the directory where the saved file is located?

src: 스타트업에서는 팀빌딩이 중요하다는데 팀빌딩이 뭐야?
mt: I heard that team building is important in startups, what is team building?
ref: They say team building is important in startups, but what is team building?

src: 이 장소의 네트워크 연결이 지연되고 있어. 무엇이 문제일까?
mt: The network connection of this place is being delayed. What is the problem?
ref: The network connection to this location is lagging. What could be the problem?

src: 고객님 죄송하지만 오션뷰 객실은 이미 예약이 끝났습니다.
mt: I'm sorry, but the reservation for the ocean view room is already complete.
ref: I'm sorry, but the ocean view rooms are no longer available.

src: 두 장소의 매력이 달라서 한 곳을 추천하기는 어렵네요.
mt: It's hard to recommend one place because the two places have different charms.
ref: It's hard to recommend one place because the two places have different charms.

src: 서울 바닐라 크림브륄레 맛집을 알려줄래?
mt: Can you tell me the Seoul Vanilla Cream Brule restaurant?
ref: Can you tell me a good vanilla crème brulee restaurant in Seoul?

src: 뮤지컬 알라딘 출연 배우들 좀 알려줄 수 있니?
mt: Can you tell me the actors who appear in the musical Aladin?
ref: Can you tell me the names of the actors in the musical Aladdin?

src: 내가 만든 디자인 시안으로 특허를 출원하는 방법을 알아봐 줘.
mt: Please find out how to apply for a patent with my design proposal.
ref: Please tell me how to apply for a patent for a design draft I created.

src: 전기차와 하이브리드는 같은 뜻인가요? 다른 뜻인가요?
mt: Does the hybrid mean the same thing as the electric car? Does it mean something else?
ref: Do electric cars and hybrids mean the same thing, or are they different?

src: 자카르타 여행할 건데 만디리 은행 박물관은 어때?
mt: I'm going to travel to Jakarta, how about the Mandiri Bank Museum?
ref: If you're traveling to Jakarta, how about visiting the Bank Mandiri Museum?

src: 발리에 여행을 가려고 하는데 발리 명소를 좀 알고 싶어.
mt: I'm trying to go on a trip to Bali, but I'd like to know some attractions in Bali.
ref: I'm planning a trip to Bali and would like to know some popular attractions.

src: 요즘은 미팅을 줌이라는 어플을 이용해서 하는 거 같애.
mt: I think we're using an application called Zoom for meetings these days.
ref: It seems like people are using an app called Zoom for meetings these days.

src: 블루투스랑 와이파이 기술이 각각 언제 발명되었는지 알고 싶어.
mt: I want to know when Bluetooth and Wi-Fi technologies were invented respectively.
ref: I'd like to know when Bluetooth and Wi-Fi technologies were each invented.

src: 호텔 예약할 거면 하노이에 있는 나의 친구한테 부탁해보자.
mt: If you're going to book a hotel, let's ask my friend in Hanoi.
ref: If you want to book a hotel, I'll ask my friend in Hanoi.

src: 그런데 평소에 그림 기법에 대해 어떤 기술을 주로 사용하시나요?
mt: But what kind of technology do you usually use for painting techniques?
ref: By the way, what kind of techniques do you usually use when it comes to drawing?

src: 내일 회의 아젠다를 업데이트해야 되는데 어떻게 해야 될까?
mt: I need to update the agenda for tomorrow's meeting, what should I do?
ref: I need to update the agenda for tomorrow's meeting. How should I do that?

src: 간단한 프로그램을 하나 만들고 싶은데 파이썬 코드를 짜줄래?
mt: I'd like to make a simple program, so could you squeeze out the pason code?
ref: I want to create a simple program. Can you write some Python code for me?

src: 넷플릭스에 탈주라는 프로그램이 있는데 지금 순위가 어떻게 될까?
mt: There is a program on Netflix called Escape, what is the ranking now?
ref: There is a show called The Escape on Netflix, I wonder what its current ranking is.

src: 특정한 주소로 스팸메일이 온다던데 무슨 주소인지 알아?
mt: I heard spam mail is coming to a specific address, do you know what it is?
ref: I heard spam emails are coming from a specific address — do you know what it is?

src: 등록 양식을 작성하면서 개인 정보와 연락처를 적어 주셔야해요.
mt: You have to write down your personal information and contact information while filling out the registration form.
ref: When you fill out the registration form, you will be asked to provide personal information and contact information.

src: 데이식스콘서트에 가고 싶은데 예매가 너무 힘들어.
mt: I want to go to the Day6 concert, but the booking is so hard.
ref: I want to go to the Day6 concert, but it's so hard to reserve tickets.

src: 이번에 여행을 갈 건데 발리에서 제일 멋진 명소를 알려줘.
mt: I'm going on a trip this time, so please tell me the best attraction in Bali.
ref: I'm going on a trip soon. Please tell me the best place to visit in Bali.

src: 발리로 해외여행 갈 건데 발리의 명소 알려줄 수 있어?
mt: I'm going abroad to Bali, can you tell me some attractions in Bali?
ref: I'm going on a trip to Bali. Can you tell me some famous places in Bali?

src: 일본 여행을 가려는데 후지산으로 패키지 여행을 계획 중이야.
mt: I'm planning a package trip to Fujisan to travel to Japan.
ref: I'm planning a trip to Japan and I'm planning a package tour to Mt. Fuji.

src: 중국의 수도인 베이징을 가려고 하는데 비행기로 얼마나 걸리지?
mt: How long does it take by plane to get to Beijing, the capital of China?
ref: I'm planning to go to Beijing, the capital of China. How long will it take by plane?

src: 트래픽을 좀 줄이는 방식으로 이 알고리즘을 변형하려면 어떻게 해야 될까?
mt: What should we do to transform this algorithm into a way to reduce traffic?
ref: How can we modify this algorithm to reduce traffic?

src: 모두 여기 타블렛에 그리기 앱을 사용하실 거에요.
mt: Everyone will use the drawing app here at the tablet.
ref: Everyone will be using the drawing app on this tablet.

src: 여기 수강생들이랑도 교류하면서 친해질 수 있고요.
mt: You can get to know each other while interacting with the students here.
ref: Here, you can become friends by interacting with the students.

src: 그래피티와 스프레이 페인트는 정말 멋진 기술이에요.
mt: Grapiti and spray paint are wonderful technologies.
ref: Graffiti and spray paint are really cool skills.

src: 이 도구는 부드러운 돌보다 단단한 돌에 더 적합합니다.
mt: This tool is more suitable for hard stones than soft stones.
ref: This tool is better suited for hard stones than soft stones.

src: 모든 힘들었던 등산이 그 순간에 모두 보상받은 것 같죠.
mt: "Every hard climb seems to have been rewarded at that moment."
ref: All the hard climbing seemed to be rewarded in that moment.

src: 강원도에 불멍하기 좋은 힐링캠핑장이 어디 있니?
mt: Where is the best healing campsite in Gangwon-do?
ref: Where is a good healing camping site in Gangwon-do?

src: 호텔 어메니티 중에 어느 호텔의 샴푸가 제일 좋아?
mt: Which hotel's shampoo is your favorite among hotel amenities?
ref: Which hotel's shampoo is your favorite among hotel amenities?

src: 구글에서 나온 픽셀 나인 프로를 사용해 본 적이 있니?
mt: Have you ever used Pixel Nine Pro from Google?
ref: Have you ever used the Pixel Nine Pro from Google?

src: 구글에서 나온 픽셀 에이트 프로를 사용해 본 적이 있니?
mt: Have you ever used Pixel Eight Pro from Google?
ref: Have you ever used the Pixel Eight Pro from Google?

src: 다양한 데이터베이스를 통해 데이터 아키텍트를 쌓아가는 곳을 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know where you are stacking data architecture through various databases.
ref: Tell me where to build your data architecture across various databases.

src: 조각은 당연 알고 계시겠지만, 창의적이고 멋진 과정이에요.
mt: As you know, sculpture is a creative and wonderful process.
ref: As you probably know, sculpture is a creative and wonderful process.

src: 팝 음악계에서 고트한 사람은 비욘세가 맞을까?
mt: Is Beyonce the gott in the pop music world?
ref: Is Beyoncé the goth person in pop music?

src: 요즘 인기 좋은 인급동의 유튜브 채널은 어떤 것들이 있어?
mt: What kind of YouTube channels are popular these days?
ref: What are some popular Ingeupdong YouTube channels these days?

src: 홀리데이 시즌에 가볼 만한 국내 여행지를 추천해 주세요.
mt: Please recommend a domestic destination to visit during the holiday season.
ref: Please recommend some domestic travel destinations to visit during the holiday season.

src: 베트남 하노이에서 묵기 편한 한국어가 통하는 호텔에 대해서 알아봐 줘.
mt: Please find out about a hotel that is easy to stay in Hanoi, Vietnam.
ref: Find out about convenient Korean-speaking hotels in Hanoi, Vietnam.

src: 우리 항저우로 여행 갔었을 때 갔던 호수 기억나?
mt: Do you remember the lake we went to when we traveled to Hangzhou?
ref: Do you remember the lake we visited when we traveled to Hangzhou?

src: 스팸메일 주소가 보통 어떤 도메인으로 끝나는지 알려줄래?
mt: Could you tell me which domain your spam address usually ends up with?
ref: Can you tell me what domains spam email addresses usually end with?

src: 데이터 모델러와 디비 엔진은 어떨 때 사용하는 거지?
mt: What do data models and DB engines use?
ref: When do you use a data modeler and a DB engine?

src: 바딘 광장에서 꼭 방문해야 할 주요 명소는 어디야?
mt: Where is the main attraction you must visit at Badin Square?
ref: What are the must-visit attractions in Ba Dinh Square?

src: 야, 고맙다. 오늘 너 덕분에 진짜 많이 배우네.
mt: Hey, thank you. I really learn a lot thanks to you today.
ref: Hey, thank you. I learned a lot today thanks to you.

src: 네, 고객님. 혹시 저희 여행사 이용이 처음이실까요?
mt: Yes, sir. Is this your first time using our travel agency?
ref: Yes, sir. Is this your first time using our travel agency?

src: 롬복으로 신혼여행을 떠날 때 드는 경비를 알려줘.
mt: Let me know the cost of going on a honeymoon to Lombok.
ref: Tell me how much it costs to go on a honeymoon to Lombok.

src: 한국은 요우커들로 인해 관광지가 항상 사람들로 붐벼.
mt: In Korea, tourist attractions are always crowded with people due to Youke.
ref: In Korea, tourist destinations are always crowded with people because of the tourists.

src: 호이안에서 사진을 예쁘게 찍을 수 있는 명소를 추천해줘.
mt: Please recommend me some attractions where I can take beautiful pictures in Hoian.
ref: Please recommend some spots in Hoi An where I can take pretty pictures.

src: 주말에 할 수 있는 랜선 투어로 어디가 좋을지 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know where would be good for the LANN tour that I can do on the weekend.
ref: Please tell me where to go for a LAN tour on the weekend.

src: 하이브리드와 전기차 중에 장거리 여행자들에게 더 추천해주는 차는 뭐야?
mt: Which car do you recommend to long-distance travelers is hybrid or electric car?
ref: Which car do you recommend for long-distance travelers: hybrid or electric?

src: 웹디자이너가 사용하는 편집 툴에는 어떤 게 있나 알려주세요.
mt: Please let me know what kind of editing tools are used by web designers.
ref: Can you let me know which editing tools are commonly used by web designers?

src: 슬랙을 이용해서 아이데이션을 효과적으로 진행하는 방법을 알려주세요.
mt: Please tell me how to effectively proceed with the foundation using slack.
ref: Please tell me how to use Slack to effectively proceed with ideation.

src: 객실 내 팜플랫 보시면 모든 메뉴 있으니까 확인해 주세요.
mt: If you look at the farm flat in the room, there are all the menus, so please check.
ref: Please check the pamphlet in your room, as it contains all the menus.

src: 설악산 정상에서 멋진 경치를 함께 감상하면 좋겠네요.
mt: I hope you enjoy the wonderful scenery at the top of Mt. Seoraksan together.
ref: It would be wonderful to enjoy the beautiful view together at the top of Seoraksan.

src: 엔비디아의 주가가 수직 상승한 이유가 뭔지 알려줄 수 있어?
mt: Can you tell me why Nvidia's stock price has risen vertically?
ref: Can you tell me why Nvidia's stock price is skyrocketing?

src: 제미니로 라이브 방송을 실시간 볼 수 있는 방법이 있어?
mt: Is there a real-time way to watch live broadcasts with Jeremy?
ref: Is there a way to watch live broadcasts in real time with Gemini?

src: 요즘 중국 쇼핑몰 테무랑 알리가 엄청 핫하다던데?
mt: I heard the Chinese shopping mall Temu and Ali are very hot these days.
ref: I heard that Chinese shopping malls Temu and Ali are super hot these days?

src: 미쉐린 가이드에서 선정한 맛집에는 스타 셰프가 있어.
mt: There is a star chef at the restaurant selected by Michelin Guide.
ref: You’ll often find star chefs working at restaurants selected by the Michelin Guide.

src: 유니콘 기업이 되려면 매출 성과 말고 다른 성과는 뭐가 필요할까?
mt: What other achievements do we need other than sales performance to become a unicorn company?
ref: What other achievements are needed to become a unicorn company, other than sales performance?

src: 세미나를 여러 번 참석하면 내가 인생 멘토가 될 수 있을까?
mt: Will I be a life mentor if I attend several seminars?
ref: If I attend several seminars, will I be able to become a life mentor?

src: 픽셀 에잇 프로와 픽셀 세븐 프로는 어떤 차이가 있어?
mt: What is the difference between Pixel It Pro and Pixel Seven Pro?
ref: What's the difference between Pixel Eight Pro and Pixel Seven Pro?

src: 자 그럼 이제부터 레이어와 브러시 사용에 대해 배울 것입니다.
mt: So from now on, I will learn about layer and brush use.
ref: Okay, now we're going to learn about using layers and brushes.

src: 이제 나름 베트남도 다양한 무역이 이루어진다고 볼 수 있지.
mt: Now, it can be said that Vietnam has various trade.
ref: We can now say that Vietnam is engaged in a fairly diverse range of trade.

src: 남자가 부른 어쿠스틱 플레이리스트 추천해줘. 많을수록 좋아.
mt: Please recommend an acoustic playlist sung by a man. The more it is, the better.
ref: Recommend me some acoustic playlists sung by men. The more the better.

src: 신칸센을 타고 일본 여행을 할 때 좋은 자리가 있어?
mt: Is there a good place to travel to Japan by Shinkansen?
ref: Is there a good seat to choose when traveling around Japan by Shinkansen?

src: 런던에 있는 메리어트 호텔의 일박 가격을 알고 싶어.
mt: I want to know the price of the Marriott Hotel in London overnight.
ref: I would like to know the price for one night at the Marriott Hotel in London.

src: 상하이 여행 중 가장 인상 깊게 본 것은 동방명주입니다.
mt: The most impressive thing I saw during my trip to Shanghai is Eastern Myeongju.
ref: The most impressive thing I saw during my trip to Shanghai was the Oriental Pearl Tower.

src: 내가 만든 이 디자인을 특허를 내고 싶은데 유효기간이 어느 정도일까?
mt: I want to issue a patent for this design that I made, how long is it valid?
ref: I want to patent this design I created, but how long is the patent period?

src: 클라이언트가 요구한 물량이 가격이랑 맞지 않으면 어떻게 해야 돼?
mt: What should I do if the quantity requested by the client doesn't match the price?
ref: What should I do if the quantity requested by the client does not match the price?

src: 픽셀 세븐 프로와 픽셀 에잇 프로의 사양 차이를 알려줘.
mt: Let me know the difference in specifications between Pixel 7 Pro and Pixel It Pro.
ref: Tell me the spec differences between the Pixel Seven Pro and Pixel Eight Pro.

src: 검색 속도는 빅데이터 검색 엔진의 성능에 따라 달라진다고 들었는데.
mt: I heard that the search speed depends on the performance of the big data search engine.
ref: I heard that search speed varies depending on the performance of the big data search engine.

src: 오늘 델타항공과 아시아나항공 중에 일본행 비행기가 있는지 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know if there is a flight to Japan between delta Airlines and Asiana Airlines today.
ref: Please let me know if there are any flights to Japan today on Delta or Asiana Airlines.

src: 관광지 투어 신청하면서 와이탄은 꼭 돌아보라고 했어.
mt: When I applied for a tour of tourist attractions, I told them to look around the Witan.
ref: When I signed up for the tourist tour, I was told to definitely visit Waitan.

src: 싱가포르 래플스 호텔 객실 중 흡연실의 객실 수를 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know the number of rooms in the smoking room of the Rapples Hotel in Singapore.
ref: Please let me know how many smoking rooms are available at Raffles Hotel in Singapore.

src: 미쉐린 가이드 식당에 스타 셰프가 상주하고 있다던데.
mt: I heard that a star chef is residing in the Michelin Guide Restaurant.
ref: I heard there's a star chef working full-time at the Michelin Guide restaurant.

src: 오늘 처갓집 양념치킨이 글로벌 시장 진출을 선언하였습니다.
mt: Today, my sister-in-law's seasoned chicken announced its entry into the global market.
ref: Today, Cheogatjip Yangnyeom Chicken announced its entry into the global market.

src: 그래서 사람들이 휴식이랑 여가 즐기러 많이들 오겠지?
mt: So many people will come to enjoy relaxation and leisure, right?
ref: So, I guess a lot of people will come here to relax and enjoy leisure time?

src: 그럼 우리 나트랑으로 리조트 잡고 여행 가는 거 어때?
mt: Then why don't we take a resort and go on a trip to Natrang?
ref: Then how about we go on a trip to Nha Trang and book a resort?

src: 최초로 바지단에 시보리를 넣어 출시한 회사는 어디였을까?
mt: Where was the first company to launch with the Seabori on the trousers?
ref: Which company was the first to introduce ribbed cuffs on its trousers?

src: 거기서 오른쪽으로 꺾어서 오분 정도 올라가면 대사관이 보일 거예요.
mt: Turn right there and go up about five minutes to see the embassy.
ref: From there, turn right and go up for about five minutes and you will see the embassy.

src: 신혼여행 가서 아기가 생기면 왜 허니문 베이비라고 해?
mt: Why do you call a honey baby when you have a baby on your honeymoon?
ref: If you go on your honeymoon and have a baby, why is it called a honeymoon baby?

src: 식사 예약을 하려면 웨이팅 리스트에 저희 이름을 남기면 될까요?
mt: Should we leave our name on the waiting list to make a reservation for a meal?
ref: If we want to make a dining reservation, can we put our names on the waiting list?

src: 탄손누트 공항에서 호치민으로 가는 방법 좀 알려줘.
mt: Please tell me how to get to Ho Chi Minh City from Tanson Nut Airport.
ref: Please tell me how to get from Tan Son Nhat Airport to Ho Chi Minh City.

src: 항구도시로 여행하고 싶은데 혹시 다낭에 가본 적 있니?
mt: I want to travel to a port city, have you ever been to Danang by any chance?
ref: I'd like to travel to a port city. Have you ever been to Danang?

src: 그럼 다른 관광지 둘러보고 와이탄에서 야경도 구경하자.
mt: Then let's look around other tourist attractions and see the night view at Witan.
ref: Then, let's go check out other tourist attractions and enjoy the night view at Waitan.

src: 중국 여행을 왔으니 치파오 입고 사진 한번 찍을래?
mt: Since I'm on a trip to China, do you want to take a picture wearing a chifao?
ref: Since you're in China, do you want to take a picture wearing a cheongsam?

src: 우리가 내일 가는 관광지에도 요우커들이 엄청 많겠지?
mt: There must be a lot of Youke in our tourist destination tomorrow, right?
ref: There will be a lot of tourists at the tourist destination we're going to tomorrow, right?

src: 우리 그럼 바딘에 도착하면 역사적인 관광도시 많이 돌아보자.
mt: Then let's look around a lot of historic tourist cities when we arrive at Badin.
ref: Then, when we arrive in Badin, let's tour many of the historical tourist cities.

src: 내용을 확인하기 위해서 크로스체크를 하고 싶은데 이에 관련된 앱이 있을까요?
mt: I want to do cross check to check the contents, is there an app related to this?
ref: I would like to cross-check the contents to confirm them. Is there an app for this?

src: 이번에 휴가를 무이네로 떠나려고 하는데 어떤 옷 입지?
mt: What clothes do you wear as I'm about to leave for Mui's this vacation?
ref: I'm planning to go on vacation to Mui Ne this time. What clothes should I wear?

src: 유튜브에서 운영하는 에이에스엠알 채널은 몇 개가 있을까?
mt: How many ASM channels do you have on YouTube?
ref: How many ASMR channels are there on YouTube?

src: 이번 여행에서 가장 쇼킹했던 모먼트는 어떤 게 있어?
mt: What was the most talked about on this trip?
ref: What was the most shocking moment on this trip?

src: 이스라엘에 있는 예루살렘은 꼭 한번 가보고 싶은 여행지이다.
mt: Jerusalem in Israel is a must-see destination.
ref: Jerusalem in Israel is a must-visit travel destination.

src: 호이안 여행을 갈 때 몇 월에 가는 게 제일 좋아?
mt: What month do you like the most when you go on a trip to Hoian?
ref: What month is best to go to Hoi An?

src: 구글에서 제미나이 첫 번째 버전은 언제 출시되었나요?
mt: When was the first version of Semina released on Google?
ref: When did Google release the first version of Gemini?

src: 엠비티아이 중에 아이에스에프제이의 특징은 뭔가요?
mt: What are the characteristics of ISCJ among the MVI?
ref: What are the characteristics of ISFJ among MBTI?

src: 싱가포르 래플즈 호텔의 별점 리뷰에 대해서 요약해줘.
mt: Please summarize the star review of the Rapples Hotel in Singapore.
ref: Please summarize the star reviews of Raffles Hotel Singapore.

src: 내 클라우드의 정보를 해킹당했을 때 제일 먼저 무엇을 해야 할까?
mt: What should I do first when my cloud information is hacked?
ref: What should I do first if my cloud information is hacked?

src: 스팸메일 주소를 내 이메일 주소록에서 지우는 방법은 무엇입니까?
mt: How can I delete the spam address from my email address book?
ref: How do I remove spam addresses from my email address book?

src: 야, 하노이에 호텔이 그렇게 죽여주게 이쁘더라.
mt: Hey, the hotel is so pretty in Hanoi.
ref: Wow, the hotels in Hanoi are so freaking beautiful.

src: 피피엘과 스폰서를 효과적으로 활용하려면 어떤 전략이 필요할까?
mt: What strategies do we need to effectively use PPL and sponsors?
ref: What strategies are needed to effectively utilize PPL and sponsors?

src: 여러 돌을 시도해보며 어떤 것이 가장 마음에 드는지 찾아보세요.
mt: Try to find out which stone you like the most.
ref: Experiment with different stones to find which one you like best.

src: 모나리자가 전시되어 있는 곳이 루브르 박물관이야?
mt: Is the Louvre Museum the place where Mona Lisa is displayed?
ref: Is the Louvre Museum where the Mona Lisa is displayed?

src: 오로라를 관측하기 좋은 여행지 세 곳만 추천해줘.
mt: Please recommend only three good tourist destinations to observe Aurora.
ref: Please recommend three great travel destinations for observing the Aurora.

src: 너 쑤저우에 여행 갔을 때 산책은 주로 어디에서 했어?
mt: Where did you usually take a walk when you went on a trip to Suzhou?
ref: Where did you mostly take walks when you were in Suzhou?

src: 제안서를 작성하기 위해 메모를 해두는 습관은 좋은 건가요?
mt: Is it a good habit to take notes to fill out a proposal?
ref: Is it a good habit to take notes when writing a proposal?

src: 이번 연도에 꽝닌으로 관광 온 인구가 몇 명이야?
mt: How many people came to visit Quang Nin this year?
ref: How many tourists came to Quang Ninh this year?

src: 나도 한번 써봐야겠다. 디테일 표현하기에 딱 좋겠는데?
mt: I should try it too. It's perfect to express details, right?
ref: I should try it too. It would be perfect for expressing details.

src: 여권 분실로 인한 추가 비용은 여행자 본인이 부담해야 하셔야 해요.
mt: The traveler has to pay extra for the loss of the passport.
ref: Any additional costs resulting from lost passports must be borne by the traveler.

src: 네, 설악산은 우리나라의 자랑스러운 자연 명소 중 하나에요.
mt: Yes, Seoraksan Mountain is one of our proud natural attractions.
ref: Yes, Seoraksan is one of our country's proud natural attractions.

src: 해안에서 채취한 여러 돌들을 가공해서 만든 팔찌가 있어요.
mt: We have bracelets made from processing various stones collected from the coast.
ref: There is a bracelet made by processing various stones collected from the coast.

src: 호텔 조식으로 스크램블이 나온 적 있는 호텔을 추천해줘.
mt: Please recommend a hotel that has a scrambles for breakfast.
ref: Recommend me a hotel that serves scrambled eggs for breakfast.

src: 용산공원 근처에서 할랄푸드 먹을 수 있는 곳 좀 알려줄래?
mt: Can you tell me a place where I can eat halal food near Yongsan Park?
ref: Can you tell me where I can eat halal food near Yongsan Park?

src: 혹시 지금 훌루에 일위 하고 있는 드라마 보신 적 있으세요?
mt: Have you ever seen the drama that is at the top of Hulu?
ref: Have you seen the drama that is currently ranked number one on Hulu?

src: 한국에 관광을 오는 중국 관광객들을 한국에서는 요우커 라고 부르고 있어.
mt: Chinese tourists who visit Korea are called Youke in Korea.
ref: In Korea, Chinese tourists who visit for sightseeing are called 'Youke'.

src: 요즘 요우커들은 어디를 어떤 관광지를 주로 다니는지 알려줘.
mt: You guys these days tell me where and which tourist attractions you usually go to.
ref: Tell me where and what tourist attractions do tourists mainly go to these days.

src: 와이탄은 중국 상해에 있는 굉장히 유명한 관광지 중에 하나야.
mt: Witan is one of the most famous tourist destinations in Shanghai, China.
ref: The Bund is one of the most famous tourist attractions in Shanghai, China.

src: 구글에서 나온 픽셀 에이트 프로라는 핸드폰에 대해서 알고 있니?
mt: Do you know about the cell phone called Pixel Eight Pro from Google?
ref: Do you know about the Pixel Eight Pro, the smartphone from Google?

src: 네. 그럼요. 잠실 주변으로는 올림픽 공원이 가기 좋아요.
mt: Yes, of course. It's good to go to Olympic Park around Jamsil.
ref: Yes, of course. Olympic Park is a good place to go around Jamsil.

src: 머라이어 캐리가 부른 캐롤 노래가 몇 개인지 알려줄래?
mt: Can you tell me how many carol songs Mariah Carey sang?
ref: Can you tell me how many Christmas carols Mariah Carey has sung?

src: 나트랑에서 가장 큰 수영장이 있는 리조트를 추천해줘.
mt: Please recommend me a resort with the largest swimming pool in Natrang.
ref: Recommend me a resort with the largest swimming pool in Nha Trang.

src: 호치민에서 꼭 가봐야 할 도시의 명소는 어디인지 알려줘.
mt: Let me know where the must-see city attraction is in Ho Chi Minh City.
ref: Tell me what are the must-see city attractions in Ho Chi Minh City.

src: 구글 미트에서 해당 사용자만 뮤트하는 방법 검색해줘.
mt: Please search for a way to mute only the user in Google Mite.
ref: Please help me find out how to mute only that user in Google Meet.

src: 링귀스트들은 프리랜서로 일할 때 주로 어떤 업무를 하게 될까?
mt: What kind of work do ringguists usually do when they work as freelancers?
ref: What kind of work do linguists usually do when they work as freelancers?

src: 데이터 아키텍트는 데이터베이스 설계 시 어떤 요소들을 가장 중요하게 고려하나요?
mt: What elements are considered most important when designing a database for data architecture?
ref: What are the most important factors that a data architect considers when designing a database?

src: 무이네 사막 완전 아름답던데. 신혼여행으로도 간대.
mt: Mui's desert was so beautiful. They're going on a honeymoon as well.
ref: Mui Ne desert is so beautiful. I recommend going there for your honeymoon.

src: 이번 휴가는 무이네로 가고 싶은데 너는 가봤니?
mt: I want to go to Muine this vacation, have you been there?
ref: I want to go to Mui Ne this vacation. Have you been there?

src: 이제 시작해볼까요? 전통 가옥의 스케치부터 시작하겠습니다.
mt: Shall we start now? Let's start with a sketch of a traditional house.
ref: Shall we begin now? Let's start with a sketch of a traditional house.

src: 오 좋은데요? 설악산 근처에는 맛있는 음식점이 많아요.
mt: Oh, that's great? There are many delicious restaurants near Seoraksan.
ref: Oh, that's good. There are a lot of delicious restaurants near Seoraksan.

src: 일본 여행 가면 도쿄에서 신주쿠 공원을 꼭 가봐.
mt: If you are traveling to Japan, make sure to go to Shinjuku Park from Tokyo.
ref: If you travel to Japan, be sure to visit Shinjuku Park in Tokyo.

src: 중국에 가게 된다면 난징에 있는 박물관에 꼭 가보고 싶네.
mt: If I go to China, I really want to visit a museum in Nanjing.
ref: If I ever go to China, I definitely want to visit the museum in Nanjing.

src: 구글 미트로 수업을 듣고 있는데 뮤트할 수 있는 방법이 뭐야?
mt: I'm taking a class with Google Mitt, how can I mute it?
ref: I'm taking a class on Google Meet. How can I mute it?

src: 유니콘 기업이 이번 연도에 성과를 어느 정도 냈는지 알고 싶어요.
mt: I want to know how much the unicorn company has achieved this year.
ref: I'd like to know how much progress the unicorn company has made this year.

src: 기업 세미나에서는 다양한 멘토들을 만날 수 있어서 좋은 거 같애.
mt: I think it's good to meet various mentors at the corporate seminar.
ref: I think it's good to be able to meet various mentors at corporate seminars.

src: 크롬브라우저는 아는데 확장 프로그램은 무슨 뜻인지 모르겠어요.
mt: I know Chrome browser, but I don't know what the extension program means.
ref: I know about Chrome browser, but I don't know what extension means.

src: 와이탄에서 야경으로 유명한 관광지는 어디를 가면 좋을까?
mt: Where should I go to a tourist attraction famous for its night view in Witan?
ref: Where should I go to a tourist attraction famous for its night view in Witan?

src: 바딘이 관광하기에 되게 좋은 장소래. 같이 놀러 가자.
mt: Badin is a great place to visit. Let's hang out together.
ref: Badin is a great place for sightseeing. Let's go and have fun together.

src: 프로젝트를 진행할 때 원하는 아웃풋을 얻기 위해 가장 중요한 요소는 무엇인가요?
mt: What is the most important factor to get the desired output when carrying out a project?
ref: When working on a project, what is the most important factor in achieving the desired output?

src: 회의록을 노션에 저장하고 싶은데 어떻게 해야 되는지 방법을 알려줘.
mt: I want to save the minutes of the meeting in the action, so please tell me how to do it.
ref: I want to save meeting minutes to Notion. Please tell me how to do that.

src: 호텔 정문에 있는 기사님에게 따로 발렛비를 주시면 돼요.
mt: You can give a separate ballet fee to the driver at the front gate of the hotel.
ref: You can pay the valet fee separately to the driver at the hotel's main entrance.

src: 외국 방송국에 뭐가 있지? 비비씨 말고는 떠오르는 게 없네.
mt: What is there in a foreign broadcasting station? Nothing comes to mind except Mr.B.
ref: Are there any other foreign broadcasting stations? The only one that comes to mind is the BBC.

src: 훌루라는 티비쇼가 있다고 들었어. 어떤 종류의 프로그램이야?
mt: I heard there's a TV show called Hulu. What kind of program is it?
ref: I heard there's a TV show called Hulu. What kind of show is it?

src: 머스크는 트럼프 대선을 지원하기 위해 수억 달러를 썼다고 해.
mt: Musk said he spent hundreds of millions of dollars to support Trump's presidential election.
ref: Musk is said to have spent hundreds of millions of dollars to support Trump's presidential campaign.

src: 요즘 줄임말이 많은데 엠지는 진짜 줄임말을 쓰는 거야?
mt: There are a lot of short words these days, but do MG really use short words?
ref: There are a lot of abbreviations these days, but does MG really use abbreviations?

src: 중국 청두 지역은 판다가 많기로 굉장히 유명한 관광 도시야.
mt: Chengdu area in China is a very famous tourist city with a lot of panda.
ref: Chengdu, China is a very famous tourist city known for having lots of pandas.

src: 신혼여행을 발리로 가는데 허니문 할 최고의 호텔 추천해줘.
mt: I'm going to Bali for my honeymoon, so please recommend me the best hotel I can enjoy.
ref: I'm going to Bali for my honeymoon. Please recommend the best hotel for my honeymoon.

src: 요즘 베트남이 무역으로 유명하지 않나? 내는 그런 걸로 아는데.
mt: Aren't Vietnam famous for trade these days? I know it's like that.
ref: Isn't Vietnam famous for trade these days? I think it's something like that.

src: 현대 아이오닉이 몇 까지 나왔더라? 그거 전기차 맞지?
mt: How many Hyundai Ionics came out? That's an electric car, right?
ref: How much has the Hyundai Ioniq been released? It's an electric car, right?

src: 엠비티아이 중에 잇프제 성향을 가진 사람의 특징을 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know the characteristics of a person who has a gum-like disposition among MVI children.
ref: Tell me the characteristics of a person with the I-P-Je tendency among MBTIs.

src: 베트남 나트랑 여행 시 가장 가성비 좋은 리조트 정보 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know the most cost-effective resort information when you travel to Nath, Vietnam.
ref: Please tell me the most cost-effective resort information when traveling to Nha Trang, Vietnam.

src: 난 패키지를 별로 안 좋아하는데 유럽 여행은 역시 패키지로 가야 될까?
mt: I don't really like packages, should I go on a trip to Europe as well?
ref: I don't really like package tours, but should I go on a package tour to Europe?

src: 내가 모아온 자료를 디렉토리에 저장하고 싶은데 어떻게 해야 하니?
mt: What should I do if I want to store the data I collected in the directory?
ref: What should I do if I want to save the materials I've collected into a directory?

src: 크리스마스에 촌캉스를 가려고 하는데 괜찮은 여행지 좀 추천해줘.
mt: I'm planning to go on a vacation at Christmas, so please recommend me a good tourist destination.
ref: I'm thinking of going on a Christmas getaway. Can you recommend some good places to visit?

src: 저번 주에 예능 프로그램에 호치민이라는 도시가 나오던데 여행해보고 싶어.
mt: There was a city called Ho Chi Minh on the entertainment show last week, and I want to travel.
ref: Last week, a city called Ho Chi Minh appeared on a TV show. I want to travel there.

src: 난 패키지가 싫은데 유럽 여행으로 자유 가는 거 어떻게 생각해?
mt: I don't like packages, so what do you think about traveling freely to Europe?
ref: I don't like package tours, but what do you think about going on a free tour of Europe?

src: 프로젝트 팔로우업하기 편한 플랫폼 찾고 있는데 추천해 줄 수 있어?
mt: I'm looking for a platform that's easy to follow up with, can you recommend one?
ref: I'm looking for a platform that's easy to follow up on projects. Can you recommend one?

src: 내가 에이아이 회사에 들어가서 파이썬으로 된 코드를 요즘 보고 있어.
mt: I'm looking at the pieon code after entering AI company these days.
ref: I'm working at an AI company and I'm looking at code written in Python these days.

src: 이번에 베트남에 있는 바딘 광장이라는 곳에 관광을 갔는데 너무 좋더라.
mt: I went to a tourist attraction called Badin Square in Vietnam and it was really good.
ref: This time I went on a tour to a place called Ba Dinh Square in Vietnam and it was really nice.

src: 도쿄 여행을 가려는데 다다미가 깔린 숙소 중 괜찮은 곳을 추천해줘.
mt: Please recommend me a nice place among the accommodations with tatami on my way to Tokyo.
ref: I'm planning a trip to Tokyo, so please recommend a good place to stay with tatami mats.

src: 호치민 가려면 너도 아마 탄손누트 공항으로 가게 될걸?
mt: If you want to go to Ho Chi Minh City, you'll probably go to Tanson Nut Airport, right?
ref: If you're going to Ho Chi Minh, you'll probably go to Tan Son Nhat Airport, right?

src: 에이아이 어시스턴트 재미나이가 무슨 뜻인지 말해줘.
mt: Tell me what AI Assistant Funny means.
ref: Tell me what the AI assistant Gemini means.

src: 호텔 어메니티 중에 샴푸를 아베다를 쓰는 호텔이 어디가 있을까?
mt: Which hotel in the hotel's amenities uses shampoos, Abeda?
ref: Which hotel uses Aveda shampoo among hotel amenities?

src: 전기차 중에 아이오닉은 인기가 있는 편인가요? 없는 편인가요?
mt: Is Ionic popular among electric vehicles? Are there any?
ref: Is the Ioniq popular among electric vehicles or not?

src: 발리에서 꼭 방문해야 할 명소에는 어떤 것들이 있는지 알려줄 수 있어?
mt: Can you tell me what kind of attractions you must visit in Bali?
ref: Can you tell me some must-visit attractions in Bali?

src: 호텔 프론트 데스크에서 수건을 빌릴 수 있는지 물어봐 주세요.
mt: Please ask if I can borrow towels at the front desk of the hotel.
ref: Please ask the hotel front desk if we can borrow a towel.

src: 이 뷰어를 보고 싶은데 어떻게 하면 액세스 권한을 가질 수 있어?
mt: I want to see this viewer, how can I get access?
ref: I want to see this viewer, how can I get access?

src: 브라우저 북마크를 다른 피씨로 이송하는 방법은 뭐가 있을까요?
mt: What is the way to transfer browser bookmark to another PC?
ref: How can I transfer my browser bookmarks to another PC?

src: 미국 오티티 훌루에서 가장 인기 있는 티비쇼는 뭐니?
mt: What is the most popular TV show in Otty Hulu, USA?
ref: What are the most popular TV shows on Hulu in the US?

src: 내 남자친구는 나이가 너무 많아서 유행이나 밈 같은 것도 다 몰라.
mt: My boyfriend is so old that he doesn't know anything about fashion or memes.
ref: My boyfriend is too old to know anything about trends or memes.

src: 프로젝트의 팔로우업 과정을 에이아이를 활용해서 자동화할 수 있을까?
mt: Can we automated the follow-up process of the project using AI?
ref: Can the follow-up process of a project be automated using AI?

src: 네, 비행기 티켓비, 유류 할증료까지 모두 포함되어 있습니다.
mt: Yes, the flight ticket fee and fuel surcharge fee are all included.
ref: Yes, the price covers the flight ticket and the fuel surcharge as well.

src: 미팅에 투머치 토커가 나왔을 때 어떻게 대응하는 것이 좋을까?
mt: How should we respond to the meeting when the Tumutch Toker comes out?
ref: How should you respond when a talker talks too much in a meeting?

src: 나트랑에서 인기 있는 리조트의 시설이나 서비스는 어떤 것들이 있어?
mt: What kind of facilities and services are popular resorts in Natrang?
ref: What facilities and services are offered at popular resorts in Nha Trang?

src: 와이탄은 역시 상하이에서 꼭 가봐야 되는 관광지 중 하나야.
mt: Witan is also one of the must-see tourist destinations in Shanghai.
ref: The Bund is definitely one of the must-visit tourist destinations in Shanghai.

src: 디럭스룸 이상 투숙객의 경우 발렛 서비스가 무료입니다.
mt: For guests with deluxe rooms or higher, the ballet service is free.
ref: Valet service is free for guests staying in deluxe rooms or higher.

src: 나는 나스닥에 투자했는데 수익을 얻었다는 사람을 본 적이 없다.
mt: I've never seen anyone invest in NASDAQ and earn money.
ref: I have never seen anyone invest in NASDAQ and make a profit.

src: 프로젝트 이후에도 클라이언트랑 꾸준히 팔로우업하는 게 중요할까?
mt: Will it be important to follow the client after the project?
ref: Is it important to continue to follow up with the client after the project?

src: 네, 늦은 시간에 놀 수 있는 곳으로 홍대나 강남을 추천해요.
mt: Yes, I recommend Hongdae or Gangnam as places where you can hang out late.
ref: Yes, I recommend Hongdae or Gangnam as places to hang out late at night.

src: 루브르 박물관에서 모나리자를 촬영하는 걸 허용하나요?
mt: Are you allowed to take Mona Lisa at the Louvre Museum?
ref: Are you allowed to take pictures of the Mona Lisa in the Louvre?

src: 요우커들이 우리나라에 와서 가장 선호하는 관광지에 대해서 알려줄 수 있을까?
mt: Can you tell me about your favorite tourist destination when you come to Korea?
ref: Could you tell me which tourist destinations are most popular among Chinese visitors to Korea?

src: 백엔드 개발에서 소프트웨어 성능 최적화를 위해 가장 중요한 요소는 무엇인가요?
mt: What is the most important factor for optimizing software performance in backend development?
ref: What is the most important factor for optimizing software performance in backend development?

src: 유후인에서 료칸으로 이박 머무실 수 있습니다.
mt: You can stay for two nights in Ryokan from the Zhuin.
ref: You can stay for two nights at a ryokan in Yufuin.

src: 원데이 클래스 중에 소금빵을 만드는 홈베이킹 클래스가 있을까요?
mt: Is there a home baking class that makes salt bread among the one-day classes?
ref: Is there a home baking class for making salt bread during the one-day class?

src: 발리에 가보고 싶은데 발리에서 꼭 가야 할 명소에 대해서 추천해줘.
mt: Please recommend a must-see attraction in Bali because I want to go to Bali.
ref: I want to go to Bali. Please recommend some must-see attractions in Bali.

src: 오늘 미팅에서 나온 안건 중에 가장 좋은 걸로 디벨롭 해줄래?
mt: Could you de-level the best agenda that came out of today's meeting?
ref: Could you develop the best of the items that came out of today's meeting?

src: 오늘 법블레스유라는 말을 들었는데 그게 도대체 무슨 말이야? 알려줘.
mt: I heard about Beopbles U today, what on earth does that mean? Tell me.
ref: I heard someone say 'Beop Bless You' today, what does that even mean?

src: 크리스마스에 촌캉스 가는 거 어떻게 생각해? 어디로 가면 좋을까?
mt: What do you think about going on a vacation at Christmas? Where should I go?
ref: What do you think about going to a countryside vacation for Christmas? Where should we go?

src: 최현석 스타 셰프가 운영하는 미쉐린 가이드 식당 위치 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know the location of the Michelin Guide Restaurant run by the star chef Choi Hyun-suk.
ref: Tell me the location of the Michelin Guide restaurant run by star chef Choi Hyun-seok.

src: 발리로 자유여행 갈 계획인데 꼭 가야 될 명소 하나 추천해줘.
mt: I'm planning to go on a free trip to Bali, so please recommend me a must-visit attraction.
ref: I'm planning a free trip to Bali. Please recommend one must-see attraction.

src: 이탈리아의 조식 좋고 오션뷰가 아주 예쁜 호텔 추천해줄래?
mt: Could you recommend a hotel with a nice breakfast and a very beautiful ocean view in Italy?
ref: Can you recommend a hotel in Italy with a good breakfast and a very pretty ocean view?

src: 성공적인 애자일 프로젝트를 위한 제품의 백로그 관리 방법을 알려줄 수 있을까?
mt: Can you tell me how to manage the backpack of the product for a successful Azail project?
ref: Could you tell me how to manage the product backlog for a successful Agile project?

src: 그래픽아트와 일러스트를 보면은 그림 그리는 사람들은 참 대단한 것 같아.
mt: When I look at graphic art and illustration, I think people who draw are amazing.
ref: When I look at graphic art and illustration, I think the people who draw are truly amazing.

src: 베트남의 항구 도시로 유명했던 다낭은 내가 오 년 전에 여행 갔었어.
mt: I traveled to Danang, which was famous as a port city in Vietnam, 5 years ago.
ref: Da Nang, a famous port city in Vietnam, was a place I visited five years ago.

src: 하노이에서 묵었던 호텔 정말 최악이었어. 시설이 너무 이상하지 않았어?
mt: The hotel I stayed in Hanoi was the worst. Isn't the facility so strange?
ref: This was the worst hotel I stayed at in Hanoi. Wasn't the facility just weird?

src: 지에스이십오와 씨유의 마케팅 전략이 궁금해. 알려줄 수 있어?
mt: I would like to know the marketing strategy of GSShipo and CU. Can you tell me?
ref: I'm curious about GS25 and CU's marketing strategies. Can you tell me?

src: 우리 회사에 새로운 시스템이 들어와서 일 년 치 플랜을 다시 짜야 돼.
mt: Our company has a new system, so we have to make a year's plan again.
ref: A new system has been introduced to our company, so we have to re-plan the year.

src: 어차피 리조트 예약해야 되면은 나트랑에 있는 거 예매하자.
mt: If we have to book a resort anyway, let's book something in Natrang.
ref: If you have to reserve a resort anyway, let's reserve one in Nha Trang.

src: 고트를 뜻하는 요즘 밈이 뭐가 있어? 유행하는 걸로 알려줄래?
mt: What kind of memes do you have these days? Can you tell me which one is in fashion?
ref: What are some current memes that refer to goth? Can you tell me what's trending?

src: 나 이번에 런던 여행 가는데 메리어트 호텔 예약 잡아줄 수 있어?
mt: I'm going on a trip to London this time, can you make a reservation for a Marriott hotel?
ref: I'm going to London this time. Can you make a reservation at the Marriott Hotel for me?

src: 회사에서 좋은 성과를 냈는데 좋은 피드백을 받지 못했어. 어떻게 해야 할까?
mt: I didn't get good feedback even though my company did a good job. What should I do?
ref: I did well at work, but I didn't get any good feedback. What should I do?

src: 요번 주 일요일은 쉬는 날이어서 호텔에 스테이케이션을 하러 가.
mt: I'm off this Sunday, so I'm going to the hotel to stay.
ref: This coming Sunday is a day off, so I'm going to a hotel for a staycation.

src: 대전으로 여행 갈 건데 소보로를 잘하는 베이커리 추천해줘.
mt: I'm going on a trip to Daejeon, so please recommend a bakery that's good at Sobo.
ref: I'm going on a trip to Daejeon. Can you recommend a bakery that makes good soboro?

src: 저번에 여행 갔다가 환전을 못 하고 온 건데 이거 위안화 동전이다?
mt: I didn't exchange money when I went on a trip last time, is this a yuan coin?
ref: I went on a trip last time and came back without being able to exchange money. Are these Yuan coins?

src: 베트남의 다른 도시들은 여행을 해봤는데 호치민은 아직 못 가봤어.
mt: I've traveled to other cities in Vietnam, but I haven't been to Ho Chi Minh yet.
ref: I've been to other cities in Vietnam, but I haven't been to Ho Chi Minh City yet.

src: 이번에 여행 어디로 갈지 고민 중인데 호이안으로 가는 거 어떻게 생각해?
mt: I'm thinking about where to travel this time, how do you think about going to Hoian?
ref: I'm thinking about where to go for my trip this time. What do you think about going to Hoi An?

src: 나는 이년 전부터 투자에 관심이 생겨서 엔비디아에 꾸준히 넣고 있어.
mt: I've been interested in investment since two years ago, so I'm constantly putting it into Nvidia.
ref: I got interested in investing about two years ago, and I've been consistently putting money into NVIDIA since then.

src: 연말이라고 플레이스테이션 세일하네. 이번 기회에 한번 사볼까?
mt: PlayStation is on sale at the end of the year. Shall we buy it this time?
ref: They're having a PlayStation sale because it's the end of the year. Should I buy one this time?

src: 요즘 메타버스랑 에이아이가 많이 나오는데 그 두 개의 차이점이 정확히 뭐야?
mt: There are a lot of children in the metaverse these days, so what exactly is the difference between the two?
ref: These days, there's been a lot of talk about the metaverse and AI — what's the exact difference between the two?

src: 새로 나온 에이아이 어시스턴트 제미나이는 어느 회사에서 만든 거야?
mt: Which company made the new AI Assistant Semina?
ref: Which company makes the new AI Assistant Gemini?

src: 파라다이스시티랑 인스파이어 리조트 중에 어디가 더 좋을까?
mt: Which do you prefer, Paradise City or Inspire Resort?
ref: Which is better, Paradise City or Inspire Resort?

src: 발리 여행할 때 빠뜨리지 말고 꼭 가봐야 할 명소들로 추천해줘.
mt: Please recommend some of the must-see attractions instead of missing them when traveling to Bali.
ref: Please recommend some must-see attractions when traveling to Bali.

src: 혹시 플레이리스트 추천해 주실 수 있으세요? 저는 어쿠스틱 음악을 참 좋아해요.
mt: Could you recommend a playlist? I really like acoustic music.
ref: Could you recommend a playlist? I really like acoustic music.

src: 데이터 사이언티스트는 어떤 걸 하는 역할이고 데이터 파이프라인은 뭐야?
mt: What role does the data scientist play and what is the data pipeline?
ref: What does a data scientist do and what is a data pipeline?

src: 링크드인에서 가장 매력적인 프로필을 작성하기 위한 방법에는 무엇이 있을까?
mt: What are the ways to write the most attractive profile in LinkedIn?
ref: How do you create the most attractive profile on LinkedIn?

src: 오늘 오전에 실시한 회의의 아젠다에 대해 업데이트해 줄 수 있어?
mt: Could you update me on the agenda of the meeting this morning?
ref: Can you update me on the agenda discussed in this morning's meeting?

src: 나는 자바 개발자라서 파이썬 코드는 거의 볼 일이 없긴 해.
mt: I'm a Java developer, so I rarely see the pison code.
ref: I'm a Java developer, so I rarely see Python code.

src: 이걸 디폴트로 해서 입력해줬으면 하는데, 도와줄 수 있으실까요?
mt: I want you to put this in as a default, can you help me?
ref: I would like to have this entered as default, can you help me?

src: 비행기가 레이오버된다고 하는데 그러면 기내식이 보통 한 끼 더 제공돼?
mt: The flight says it's a layover, so do you usually have one more meal?
ref: If the flight has a layover, do they usually provide an extra meal?

src: 신혼여행으로 발리에 갔을 때 다니기 좋은 관광 명소에 대해서 알려줘.
mt: Tell me about the tourist attractions that are good to visit when you go to Bali for your honeymoon.
ref: Please tell me about good tourist attractions to visit when going to Bali for honeymoon.

src: 인생 멘토를 가장 많이 만날 수 있는 세미나에 참석하려면 어떻게 해야 할까?
mt: What should I do to attend a seminar where I can meet life mentors the most?
ref: How do I get into a seminar where I can meet the most life mentors?

src: 소프트웨어와 하드웨어의 차이점은 뭐고 백엔드가 뭔지 설명해줄래?
mt: Could you explain the difference between software and hardware and what the backend is?
ref: Can you explain the difference between software and hardware and what the backend is?

src: 중국 여행 갔을 때 치파오 입고 사진 찍어보지 못한 게 좀 아쉬워.
mt: I'm a bit disappointed that I couldn't take a picture with the Chipao on my trip to China.
ref: I regret not taking a picture wearing a cheongsam when I traveled to China.

src: 중국 난징에 갔다가 박물관을 우연히 갔었거든? 정말 넓더라고.
mt: Did you happen to go to the museum when you went to Nanjing, China? It was really wide.
ref: I happened to go to a museum in Nanjing, China. It was really big.

src: 후쿠오카 리츠칼튼 호텔 조식에는 스크램블이 있나요?
mt: Do you have a scrambles in Fukuoka Ritz-Carlton hotel breakfast?
ref: Does The Ritz-Carlton, Fukuoka have scrambled eggs for breakfast?

src: 내가 이번에 대구로 관광 갔는데 요우커들이 겁나 많더라구.
mt: I went to Daegu for a tour this time and you guys were scared.
ref: I went to Daegu for sightseeing this time, and there were a lot of foreigners there.

src: 이번 프로젝트에서 디벨롭이 필요할 것 같은데 내일 미팅해보는 거 어때요?
mt: I think we need a developer for this project, so why don't we have a meeting tomorrow?
ref: I think we need to further develop this project — how about having a meeting tomorrow?

src: 스프레드시트를 드라이브에 저장한 후 다른 사람과 어떻게 공유할 수 있나요?
mt: How can I share the spreadsheet with others after storing it on the drive?
ref: How can I share a spreadsheet with others after saving it to the shared drive?

src: 프로젝트 진행 상황을 팔로우업할 때 쓰기 좋은 툴이 있다면 좀 알려줘.
mt: Please let me know if there is a good tool to use when following up the progress of the project.
ref: Could you let me know if there is a good tool for managing or tracking project progress?

src: 잘 되어가고 있긴 한데, 음 미안한데 물감을 좀 빌려도 될까?
mt: It's going well, but I'm sorry but can I borrow some paint?
ref: It's going well, but, um, sorry, can I borrow some paint?

src: 라우터를 설치했는데도 와이파이가 잘 안 터지면 어떤 걸 바꿔야 돼?
mt: What should I change if the Wi-Fi doesn't work even though I installed the router?
ref: What should I change if the WiFi isn't working well even after installing the router?

src: 오키나와 여행 갔는데 거기는 렌트카가 없으면 아무 데도 못 가겠더라.
mt: I went on a trip to Okinawa, but I couldn't go anywhere without a rental car.
ref: I went on a trip to Okinawa, but I couldn't go anywhere there without a rental car.

src: 유후인 여행을 가고 싶은데 인기가 많은 료칸을 추천해줄래?
mt: I'd like to go on a trip to the U.S., so could you recommend a popular Ryokan?
ref: I want to go on a trip to Yufuin. Can you recommend a popular ryokan?

src: 호텔에 캐리어를 미리 맡기고 싶은데 컨시어지에 가서 부탁하면 될까?
mt: I want to leave my luggage to the hotel in advance, so can I go to the concierge and ask for it?
ref: I want to leave my luggage at the hotel in advance. Can I go to the concierge and ask?

src: 베트남에 있는 호치민 탄손누트 공항은 시설이 어때? 깔끔하니?
mt: How's the facility at Tanson Nut Airport in Ho Chi Minh, Vietnam? Is it clean?
ref: How are the facilities at Tan Son Nhat Airport in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam? Is it clean?

src: 이번에 새로 산 스투시 슬리브 입고 감성 카페 가서 사진 찍고 싶다.
mt: I want to go to an emotional cafe and take a picture wearing a new Stush slip.
ref: I want to wear the new Stussy sleeves I bought this time and go to a sentimental cafe to take pictures.

src: 친구랑 휴가 가려고 하는데 무이네에서 할 수 있는 가장 재밌는 게 뭐야?
mt: I'm going on a vacation with my friend, what's the most interesting thing you can do in Mui's?
ref: I'm planning a vacation with a friend, what's the most fun thing to do in Mui Ne?

src: 중국에서는 사업을 할 때 <unk>시가 가장 중요하다는데 <unk>시가 도대체 뭐야?
mt: In China, it is said that the most important thing is to do business, but what on earth is it?
ref: They say guanxi is the most important thing when doing business in China, but what exactly is guanxi?

src: 사이공 거리 걸으면서 맥주 한 잔 하면은 그날 여행 피로 다 풀려.
mt: A glass of beer while walking on Saigon Street will be released from fatigue that day.
ref: A beer while walking through the streets of Saigon will wash away all the fatigue from the day's travel.

src: 내용이 맞는지 확인하려고 크로스체크를 할 건데 다른 자료랑 어떻게 비교하면 될까?
mt: I'm going to cross check to see if the content is correct, how can I compare it with other data?
ref: I'm going to cross-check to make sure the content is correct, but how can I compare it to other sources?

src: 저 지금 투잡 뛰고 있는데 이러다가 엔잡러 되는 거 아닌지 모르겠어요.
mt: I'm running two jobs right now, and I'm not sure if I'm going to get into something like this.
ref: I'm working two jobs right now, and I'm not sure if I'll end up a part-timer.

src: 베트남 여행 때문에 환전하려고 보니까 백 동에 오 점 오구원이래.
mt: I tried to exchange money for my trip to Vietnam, but it's a five-way shop that came in 100 dong.
ref: When I was trying to exchange money for my trip to Vietnam, I saw that there were 5 points and 59 won for 100 dong.

src: 이번에 홋카이도로 여행을 가는데 이제 겨울이잖아. 그래서 나베 요리를 먹으려고.
mt: I'm going on a trip to Hokkaido this time. It's winter now. So I'm going to have a nabe dish.
ref: I'm going on a trip to Hokkaido this time, and it's winter now. So I'm planning to eat nabe.

src: 메타버스와 에이아이의 결합이 이루어진다면 기대해볼 수 있는 효과는 뭘까?
